The paper deals with the problem of graph reachability in directed layered planar graphs, which is a topic in graph algorithms and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some combinatorial aspects, such as the use of planar separators, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category. The problem of graph reachability is a fundamental problem in theoretical computer science, and the paper makes progress towards resolving an important open question, which could make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
